In docs/app/global.css, remove lines 462-473 (the second @media (max-width: 639px) block at the end of the file). This block globally overrides .shadow-md and .shadow-lg utility classes on mobile, which silently changes the meaning of Tailwind utilities. Keep the first @media (max-width: 639px) block (lines 446-455) — that one targets the search dialog by selector, which is fine.

The block to remove:
```
/* Reduce shadow offsets on mobile for retro components with shadow-md (4px) or larger.
 * The RetroUI offset shadow consumes significant horizontal/vertical space on narrow screens.
 * Downgrade shadow-md → shadow-xs (1px) and shadow-lg → shadow-sm (2px) below sm breakpoint. */
@media (max-width: 639px) {
  .shadow-md {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-xs);
  }

  .shadow-lg {
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }
}
```
